sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K112022
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Lambda phage lysis device - no promoter
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This variation uses PconC5 to drive the production of antiholin. ---- This part is in BBb Format. It is flanked by BamHI and BglII sites instead of XbaI and SpeI. More information about the BBb Format is available at:
[http://openwetware.org/wiki/Template:AndersonLab:BBb_Standard BBb Standard Description Page]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bing Xia
